---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service" description="Terms of Service for the Open Working Hours mobile app.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-stone-900">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-2">Last updated: January 2026</p>
      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-1">
        <a href="/de/terms" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">Deutsche Version (Nutzungsbedingungen)</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
      <!-- Note for legal review -->
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-8 not-prose">
        <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm">
          <strong>Note:</strong> This document is a draft prepared for legal review. Final version pending approval by qualified legal counsel.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 1. Introduction -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">1. Introduction and Acceptance</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Open Working Hours mobile application ("App")
          operated by Lukas Jonathan Hondrich ("we", "us", "our").
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          By creating an account or using the App, you agree to these Terms and our
          <a href="/app-privacy-policy" class="text-teal-600">Privacy Policy</a>.
          If you do not agree, please do not use the App.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Service Description -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">2. Service Description</h2>
        <p>Open Working Hours provides:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>A mobile app for tracking working hours using geofencing and manual input</li>
          <li>Calendar functionality for planning shifts and absences</li>
          <li>The ability to confirm and submit daily working hours</li>
          <li>Contribution to anonymized, aggregated statistics about healthcare working conditions</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The App is designed for healthcare workers in Germany who wish to track their working hours
          and contribute to transparent reporting on working conditions in the healthcare sector.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Account -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">3. Account Registration</h2>
        <p>To use the App, you must:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Provide a valid email address for verification</li>
          <li>Complete your profile with your federal state, medical specialty, and role level</li>
          <li>Be at least 18 years old or have the legal capacity to enter into this agreement</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account and for all activities
          that occur under your account.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Consent to Aggregation -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">4. Consent to Data Aggregation</h2>
        <p>
          By using the App and submitting confirmed working hours, you consent to your data being included
          in aggregated, anonymized statistics. These statistics:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Contain no personal data that can identify you</li>
          <li>Are only published when groups meet minimum size thresholds (k-anonymity)</li>
          <li>May be shared publicly or with healthcare unions, professional associations, and researchers</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You may withdraw this consent at any time by deleting your account. Upon deletion, your personal
          data will be removed, but previously calculated aggregated statistics will be retained as they
          cannot be linked back to you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Acceptable Use -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">5. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Provide accurate information about your working hours</li>
          <li>Use the App only for its intended purpose</li>
          <li>Not attempt to manipulate or falsify data</li>
          <li>Not attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, or interfere with the App's operation</li>
          <li>Not use the App for any unlawful purpose</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms or that we
          reasonably believe are submitting fraudulent data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. Data Accuracy -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">6. Data Accuracy and Responsibility</h2>
        <p>
          You are responsible for the accuracy of the working hours you submit. The App provides tools
          (geofencing, calendar) to help you track time, but the final confirmation of daily hours is your responsibility.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The aggregated statistics we publish are based on user-submitted data. We do not independently
          verify individual submissions. The statistics should be understood as self-reported data from
          healthcare workers, not officially audited records.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 7. Intellectual Property -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The App, its design, code, and content are owned by us and protected by intellectual property laws.
          You may not copy, modify, distribute, or create derivative works from the App without our permission.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The aggregated statistics we produce may be used freely for non-commercial purposes with attribution
          to Open Working Hours. Commercial use requires our prior written consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 8. Disclaimer -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not guarantee that:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>The App will be available at all times without interruption</li>
          <li>The App will be free of errors or bugs</li>
          <li>The geofencing feature will work perfectly in all locations</li>
          <li>The aggregated statistics will be complete or representative of all healthcare workers</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 9. Limitation of Liability -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, we shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
          special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the App.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This includes but is not limited to: damages arising from disputes with your employer about
          working hours, reliance on aggregated statistics, or any actions taken based on data from the App.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 10. Employer Independence -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">10. Independence from Employers</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Open Working Hours is not an employer tool.</strong> We have no relationship with your employer.
          Your employer:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Cannot access your individual data</li>
          <li>Cannot request access to your data from us</li>
          <li>Has no role in operating or governing this service</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This App is designed to empower healthcare workers, not to serve as an employer monitoring system.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 11. Changes -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">11. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you
          through the App. Your continued use of the App after changes take effect constitutes acceptance
          of the new Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 12. Termination -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">12. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          You may terminate your account at any time by using the delete account function in the App.
          We may terminate or suspend your account if you violate these Terms.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Upon termination, your personal data will be deleted in accordance with our Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 13. Governing Law -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">13. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the Federal Republic of Germany. Any disputes arising
          from these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Berlin, Germany.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 14. Contact -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-4">14. Contact</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms, contact:</p>
        <address class="not-italic mt-2 text-stone-700">
